answers.answer: Possibly a sign of preeclampsia... your dr. would aware you if anything was seriously wrong & suggest treatment. But sometimes it just happens-try resting & staying extremely hydrated. If that doesn't work & other symptoms develop(light headed, cold sweats, clammy skin, nausea, abfominal pain) yhrn I woild definitely go in or at least call. Happened to me & I did nothing, when my dr. Heard about it told me I should've come in immediately. Luckily me & baby were fine. Hope tou feel better! ☺
